Assume 1 pound = 1.64 USD and 1 euro = 1.32 USD, and round to the nearest whole number.

ost_step.2: To convert the amount of pounds into euros, first convert pounds to USD using the exchange rate: 1 pound = 1.64 USD, so 150 pounds = 150 * 1.64 = 246 USD.
ost_step.3: Then, convert the USD to euros using the other exchange rate: 1 euro = 1.32 USD, so 246 USD = 246 / 1.32 ≈ 186 euros.
ost_step.4: Now, to determine how many more euros Kathy will have than pounds, compare the amounts of euros and pounds, which are approximately 186 and 150.
